    test(002EYA): operator baseline capture — commit Playwright visual baselines, fix ambiguous locators, deterministic e2e DB
    
    Operator step for slice 002EYA (agent sandboxes cannot run browsers):
    - Commit the six screenshot baselines required by 002EY/002EYA: login,
      authenticated dashboard, tracer closed state, missing-session login,
      invalid-login error, and zero-permission dashboard (chromium/darwin).
    - Fix strict-mode locator collisions found on first real browser run:
      getByRole name matching is substring-based, so 'Tracer' also matched the
      profile button of the user named 'E2E Tracer Staff'; positive assertions
      now use exact: true.
    - Delete the isolated e2e sqlite DB before each suite run so entity sequence
      numbers (MEM-000001, ...) are identical every run; the tracer-closed
      baseline depends on that determinism.
    
    Verified: npx playwright test --update-snapshots green, then npm run e2e
    passed twice consecutively in normal comparison mode. typecheck and lint
    clean. Remaining 002EYA scope (E2E_DJANGO_PYTHON fail-fast, seed_e2e_users
    guard + tests) stays with the agent slice.
    
